post_text:
FCPS continues to monitor the situation regarding the COVID-19 pandemic. This situation is changing rapidly and we are monitoring the information as it is released by the health department, CDC, and VDOE.

At this time, we are postponing all trips outside of Floyd County for students and staff. Volunteers who have traveled outside the area are asked to contact the School Board Office before reporting to a school campus. This includes student teachers, field study students, and any community volunteer.

We are planning for the extended closing of schools should it be necessary. Schools will be closed for students on Monday, March 16, 2020. Staff will report to their schools for a workday to prepare remote learning activities. Schools will reopen for students on Tuesday, March 17, 2020.
Information will continue to be shared on our website, app, and social media accounts.

https://www.floyd.k12.va.us/covid19

#floydschools

The Spring FBLA Region Conference was last week at Roanoke College. Congratulations to all of our students who are advancing to compete at the FBLA State Leadership Conference in April! We have 25 students who are advancing!!! FCHS students will also hold 4 of 7 region officer positions for the 2020-2021 school year - Brook Smith, Vice President; Isaiah Hawkins, Treasurer; Cooper Nolen, Parliamentarian; and Grace Wood, Historian. So proud of our Future Business Leaders of America!

shared_text:
Floyd County High School
February 24 at 9:30 AM ·

Our FFA team competed in a horse judging and hippology competition at Virginia Tech last weekend, hosted by the Block and Bridle Club at Virginia Tech. This contest involved ranking classes of horses, solving a team problem, equipment id, and oral reasons. Our students competed and had a blast. We placed 9th both days out of over 30 teams. Way to go, FFA!

This contest involved ranking classes of horses, solving a team problem, equipment id, and oral reasons. Our students competed and had a blast. We placed 9th both days out of over 30 teams. Way to go, FFA!

shared_text:
Floyd County High School
November 7, 2019 at 4:04 PM ·

Today was the 3rd Annual Career Fair at Floyd County High School! We were pleased to have had our largest number of local businesses (almost 50!) to set up and engage our students! Students were able to interact and learn about our local professions varying in industry. After the Career Fair, businesses were invited to participate in a Workforce Forum hosted by our Economic and Development Authority Team. In addition, we had 28 students who were invited to interview for current job openings.
Thank you to all of vendors and businesses for participating! You are each a valuable part of our community and the development of our students!

shared_text:
Floyd County Economic Development Authority
November 7, 2019 at 4:42 PM ·

Students from Floyd County High School participated in the 3rd Annual Career Fair. There was a great turnout from local businesses set up for students to meet and learn more about potential careers and industries. Students also had the opportunity to sign up for interviews for current job openings in the community. Following the Career Fair, business leaders were invited to attend a Workforce Forum led by Floyd County Economic Development Staff. We would like to thank all the businesses, organizations, and business leaders for participating and taking time to engage with Floyd students. We would also like to thank the Floyd County High School staff and administration for all of their work for a successful Career Fair! #yesFloydVA #futureworkforce

September 10, 2019 at 11:32 AM ·

Meet the Band Van! We are thrilled to be able to donate this van to the FCHS Band. It will tow the trailer full of instruments to all band performances.
"Whenever we find our fleet has surplus vehicles, we could trade those in, but the trade in value is so low, and we've determined that we get a better use by reusing that vehicle in the community for various needs such as the School System, Plenty!, the Rec Department. We've done several things over the years, and we like to see these vehicles remain in the community to benefit the community." -Greg Sapp, General Manager of Citizens

"Floyd County is a beautiful place and the enhancements the FCPS staff and school board are making align wonderfully with the positive direction public education is going in our state. The increased opportunities Dr. Wheeler and his team are creating for students along with the facility improvements like the Collaboration and Career Development Center are very impressive." Dr. James Lane, Superintendent of Public Instruction.

Thanks to all of the great work by our School Board and Board of Supervisors! #floydschools

April 15, 2019 at 8:20 AM ·

Very proud of our SkillsUSA Team and their sponsors! Floyd County students traveled to Virginia Beach for the SkillsUSA State Leadership and Skills Conference.

1st Place, Principles of Engineering/Technology- Riley Spanger
1st Place, Robotics/Urban Search and Rescue- Owen MacWoodard-Vladyka, Micyah Wahlberg
2nd Place, Technical Drafting- Logan Robertson
2nd Place, Power Equipment Technology- Jacob Dowd
2nd Place, Engineering Design- Zach Boyd, David Vaden, Cameron Parker
Silver in Technical Exams- Logan Robertson, Shawn Farris, Jacob Dowd

The students showed their skills and abilities! Riley, Owen, and Micyah will now compete, representing Virginia, at the National stage in June! Congratulations to our SkillsUSA Team!!

post_text:
FLOYD COUNTY SCHOOL BOARD VACANCY ANNOUNCEMENT
The Floyd County School Board is seeking candidates for the interim appointment of the Locust Grove District School Board seat for an intervening term beginning in May 2019 through December 31, 2019 to fill the vacancy of resigning School Board Member Maria “Faye” Nichols. In accordance with the Code of Virginia, Section 24.2-228, when a vacancy occurs, the School Board shall appoint a qualified voter and resident of the election district in which the vacancy occurs.

Interested applicants residing in the Locust Grove District of Floyd County, Virginia, are invited to submit a letter of interest to the Floyd County School Board Office to the attention of the Floyd County School Board Clerk, Janet C. Harris, at 140 Harris Hart Rd. NE, Floyd, VA 24091. Letters of interest will be accepted until April 18, 2019 at 4:00 p.m. The Floyd County School Board will conduct interviews of the interested parties at a date and time to be determined. Any inquiries should be directed to Mr. James Ingram, School Board Chairman (540-597-7472).

post_text: Congratulations Ms. Agnew!
shared_text:
Shelor Motor Mile
December 14, 2017 at 10:33 AM ·

Ms. Joan Agnew was the lucky winner of our Teacher of the Month contest from Willis Elementary! Ms. Agnew has been a teacher for 39 years and currently is in Special Education. Ms. Agnew always puts her kids first. When she battled cancer, she never missed a single day! She scheduled everything around her school schedule because she wanted her children to have a normal day. This is just one of the many special things she does! We are thankful for teachers like Ms. Agnew that lead our youth to a brighter future 📚 #growingthefuture #msagnewisasuperhero Willis Elementary School

post_text:
We live in a world surrounded by technology. And we know that whatever field our students choose to go into as adults, their ability to succeed will increasingly depend on understanding how technology works.

But only a tiny fraction of us are learning how technology works. Fewer than half of all schools teach computer science. So today FCPS is celebrating The Hour of Code along with over 100 million students worldwide!

https://goo.gl/ttjA9E
